race.comment: I'M LUCKY TWO (4) put back-to-back wins together before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Gets 2kg off with the claim and maps ideally from gate two. Plenty to like about his prospects. KWAMI (1) has placed two from two around this circuit and will strip fitter second-up from the break. Looms as the main danger. SPARTUS (3) boasts a win over this course and distance and gets the deadly Gollan/Jones combination. Watch for sharp improvement on that first-up effort. HOKUSAI (7) five-year-old mare who drops in journey from the latest effort when fourth over 1000m at Taroom, finishing 3 lengths off the winner. In the mix.
